# Transient edition-diff review scratch (fold into errata.yml, then delete)
**/errata.candidates.yml

# Book folders — track ONLY the derived digital edition (root .mdx + their *_media/).
# Everything else stays out of git: the Word/PDF sources, the GasunsDhatu_2014 PhD-defense
# dump (~281 MB of PDFs, .xlsm, .rar/.zip, ВАК paperwork) and the Talmud prior-conversion
# scratch (_raw/_pipe .md, chunks/, local notes). Ignore-all-except is used deliberately so
# a stray `git add -A` can never sweep the bulk in; the artifacts are re-included below.
# (gitignore never untracks an already-tracked file, so committed .mdx/_media are safe.)
GasunsDhatu_2014/*
!GasunsDhatu_2014/*.mdx
!GasunsDhatu_2014/*_media/
# H246 print-prep: errata pair + working notes for the 2026 edition (.md — not published by the site)
!GasunsDhatu_2014/errata.yml
!GasunsDhatu_2014/ERRATA.md
!GasunsDhatu_2014/revision-2026/
TolchelnikovTalmud_2026/*
!TolchelnikovTalmud_2026/*.mdx
!TolchelnikovTalmud_2026/IMPROVEMENT_PLAN.md
!TolchelnikovTalmud_2026/student-roadmap.md
!TolchelnikovTalmud_2026/visual-grammar.md
!TolchelnikovTalmud_2026/talmud-refactoring.md
# H242 scaffold: errata pair, session journal, human-gated footnote proposals
!TolchelnikovTalmud_2026/errata.yml
!TolchelnikovTalmud_2026/ERRATA.md
!TolchelnikovTalmud_2026/.ai_state.md
!TolchelnikovTalmud_2026/footnote-proposals/
# H241 Phase-3 enrichment crosswalk: derived data asset + reproducible generators
!TolchelnikovTalmud_2026/data/
!TolchelnikovTalmud_2026/tools/
# H329: raw /z/ scrape cache stays local (guardrail — commit only the derived join map)
TolchelnikovTalmud_2026/data/raw_cache/
